data.name: chk_equaPool3.ToolTip
data.value:
Equalizes the drop chance for every item when this pool is drawn. If you want every items in this pool, for this generation of loot, to have the same chance to drop then check this.
Example :
If you have a pool with Item1, Item2 and Item3, they will, once you check this, all have 33% drop chance.

data.name: label1.ToolTip
data.value:
Input here a chance, on 100%, that the item pool associated (on the left) will be drawn when generating loot.
For example, if you decide to put item pool A with a chance of 75 and item pool B with a chance of 25, then there will be a 75% chance that each item looted comes from pool A and 25% chance that it comes from pool B.

data.name: lbl_itemRarity.ToolTip
data.value:
This is the rarity of the item drawn. This reflects the quality of an item.
Higher letter is better, except for S, which is considered the highest letter.
The rarities, in order of most common to rarest, goes as follow : F,E,D,C,B,A,S,SS,SSS (SSS being the rarest, F being the most common)

data.name: lbl_dropChanceMod.ToolTip
data.value:
Modifies the drop chance of each item, in every pool, by a set modifier.
Example: If an item has 50% chance to be generated and you put a modifier of 2X, then the item will have 100% chance to be generated.
